New Records: Devin Booker scored 34 points, matching his season average with a strong performance against the Jazz.
Key Match Events: Grayson Allen hit a crucial three-pointer in the fourth quarter to extend the Suns' lead, sealing the victory.
Post-Match Reflections: The Suns have now won three of their last four games, showing improved form under coach Mike Budenholzer's new rotation.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played at the Footprint Center in front of 17,071 fans, with the Suns' 114-106 victory moving them to 18-19 on the season.
Others: The Jazz were without several key players, including Jordan Clarkson and John Collins, as they continued their slide with a third consecutive loss.
